flowchart LR

  subgraph WHY["1. Why this group exists"]
    W1["The platform cannot stop at runtime truth and label truth"]
    W2["It also has to turn those truths into a governed learning corridor that produces a causal learning basis, an authoritative dataset, a candidate bundle, a governed promotion decision, and finally the runtime authority the decision fabric is supposed to consume"]
    W3["The design authority and readiness docs make that sequence explicit"]
    W4["The learning and evolution plane is pinned to an offline-dataset surface, a managed train and eval surface, and an explicit governed promotion, rollback, and activation-authority surface"]
    W5["It is governed by a strict temporal-realism contract: runtime stays causal, learning only reads archive plus truth through replay basis, feature as-of, label as-of, and label-maturity controls, and any future-timestamp leakage is fail-closed"]
  end

  subgraph PATHS["2. Why the five paths are justified together"]
    P1["Learning-input basis path"]
    P2["Offline dataset commitment path"]
    P3["Train / eval and candidate-bundle path"]
    P4["Promotion and rollback-governance path"]
    P5["Active-bundle authority feedback path"]
    P6["Learning-input basis proves archive truth, label truth, and replay references are not enough by themselves; the platform first pins a causal learning basis with replay basis, as-of, maturity, and anti-leakage controls"]
    P7["Offline dataset commitment proves the offline-dataset corridor does not merely run managed jobs; it commits authoritative dataset truth with deterministic manifests, fingerprints, rollback recipes, and time-bound and leakage audits"]
    P8["Train / eval and candidate-bundle proves the train and eval corridor does not merely produce model artifacts; it produces provenance-complete candidate truth through managed train/eval with explicit leakage, quality, and lineage closure"]
    P9["Promotion and rollback-governance proves the promotion corridor does not treat promotion as a boolean flag; it runs a governed corridor with explicit promotion evidence, rollback drill truth, bounded rollback objectives, active-resolution checks, and no shadow promotion path"]
    P10["Active-bundle authority feedback proves promoted registry truth is not yet runtime authority until it is deterministically resolved for the runtime that will consume it"]
    P11["Taken together, the five paths prove Group 6 is a bounded truth system with five distinct owned outcomes rather than the ML stack in some vague sense"]
  end

  subgraph CLAIM["3. Group-level claim"]
    G1["The platform turns authoritative runtime and label truth into governed model-evolution truth, and then turns governed promoted state back into deterministic runtime decision authority"]
    G2["The current wired system has explicit truths for learning basis, dataset identity, candidate identity, promotion truth, rollback truth, and runtime authority feedback"]
    G3["That makes the system look like a genuine learning-and-activation architecture rather than jobs and registries loosely connected together"]
  end

  subgraph PROOF["4. What this group proves for A"]
    A1["Strongest closure: continuity, safety, and uniqueness"]
    A2["Continuity closes because the learning corridor is explicit: archive and runtime truth plus label truth to pinned replay/as-of/maturity basis to offline dataset truth to train and eval truth to candidate-bundle truth to promotion and rollback truth to active-bundle runtime authority"]
    A3["The cross-plane definitions split the corridor the same way: runtime and case/label truth into learning, learning into registry and promotion, registry back into runtime authority"]
    A4["Safety closes because there is no future leakage, no hidden placeholder shortcuts, no hidden local or script-only learning path, no promotion without complete lineage, no rollback path that exists only on paper, and no runtime adoption that drifts silently from promoted registry truth"]
    A5["Uniqueness closes because the system pins one replay-basis receipt, one immutable dataset fingerprint per basis, one candidate bundle per governed train/eval closure, one governed promotion corridor, and one deterministic active-bundle resolution per consuming runtime scope"]
    A6["It also gives strong existence closure because these are materially seated in run-scoped learning-input evidence surfaces, Databricks plus Iceberg and Glue, SageMaker plus MLflow, the managed promotion corridor with concrete promotion, rollback, and active-resolution artifacts, and explicit runtime-facing active-resolution snapshots"]
  end

  subgraph AMBIG["5. A ambiguities to carry upward"]
    M1["The biggest A ambiguity is explanatory"]
    M2["We need to keep very clear the difference between learning-input truth, dataset truth, candidate truth, promotion truth, and runtime authority truth"]
    M3["The design intentionally separates these, but an outsider could easily collapse them into one generic ML pipeline story if synthesized lazily"]
    M4["There is also a current-wired nuance to state honestly: the semantic objective of the group is very stable, but some managed closure history includes advisory or implementation-specific detail around exact execution shapes"]
    M5["That does not weaken A, but the synthesis should keep the emphasis on the owned truth boundaries rather than every tactical execution wrinkle"]
  end

  subgraph PARK["6. Bi spillover to park"]
    B1["Questions about managed train/eval durations and success rates, rollback recovery targets under repeated promotion pressure, active-bundle resolution stability under broader runtime churn, and whether the bounded labeled slice scales cleanly to larger learning windows belong later in Bi"]
    B2["For A, Group 6 only needs to prove that the current wired platform has a real, intentional, and materially seated learning-and-activation truth system, not yet that every managed lane has been pressure-proven at the final production envelope"]
  end

  subgraph VERDICT["7. Group verdict"]
    V1["Group 6 proves that the platform does not merely train models; it constructs a governed learning-and-activation corridor that turns platform truth into model-evolution truth and then back into runtime decision authority"]
    V2["This is a major A win because the current wired system has a genuine ML platform architecture: not just datasets, jobs, and registry entries, but explicit truths for causal basis, dataset identity, candidate bundles, promotion and rollback governance, and deterministic runtime authority"]
  end

